<subSubSection pageId="11" pageNumber="114" type="key">
<paragraph blockId="11.[151,1436,1012,1180]" box="[151,924,1012,1034]" pageId="11" pageNumber="114">
a) male: genitalia as 
<figureCitation box="[400,475,1012,1034]" captionStart="FIGURE 3" captionStartId="7.[151,250,1943,1967]" captionTargetBox="[214,1368,208,1916]" captionTargetId="figure-18@7.[203,1383,181,1919]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="FIGURE 3. A–B. Genitalia, ventral view; A. Ceropales pallida sp. nov.; B. C. maculata. C–D. Subgenital plate (sternite 8) of male, dorsal view; C. Ceropales pallida sp. nov.; D. C. maculata. E–F. Subgenital plate (sternite 8) of male, lateral view; E. Ceropales pallida sp. nov.; F. C. maculata." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6770940" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6770940/files/figure.png" pageId="11" pageNumber="114">Fig. 3A</figureCitation>
; clypeus of uniform light coloration (
<figureCitation box="[835,913,1012,1034]" captionStart="FIGURE 2" captionStartId="6.[151,250,1147,1171]" captionTargetBox="[152,1436,181,1123]" captionTargetId="figure-25@6.[151,1436,181,1123]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="FIGURE 2. A–B. Head of male in frontal view; A. Ceropales pallida sp. nov.; B. C. maculata. C–D. Head of female in dorsal view; C. Ceropales pallida sp. nov.; D. C. maculata." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6770938" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6770938/files/figure.png" pageId="11" pageNumber="114">Fig. 2A</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="11.[151,1436,1012,1180]" pageId="11" pageNumber="114">
- female: antennal segment 1 (scapus) more slender, distinctly longer than broad; tibia 3 with at most only apical edge darkened (
<figureCitation box="[233,306,1071,1093]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="5.[151,250,1943,1967]" captionTargetBox="[374,1216,183,1919]" captionTargetId="figure-18@5.[371,1216,181,1919]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURE 1. A–C. Habitus of Ceropales. A. Holotype male, Ceropales pallida sp. nov.; B. Female, C. pallida sp. nov; C. Female, C. maculata." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6770936" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6770936/files/figure.png" pageId="11" pageNumber="114">Fig. 1B</figureCitation>
).................................................................................... 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Ødegaard &amp; Abenius &amp; Paukkunen" authorityYear="2022" box="[1340,1436,1070,1092]" class="Insecta" family="Pompilidae" genus="Ceropales" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="11" pageNumber="114" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="pallida">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[1340,1436,1070,1092]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="114">C. pallida</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="11.[151,1436,1012,1180]" box="[151,1014,1100,1122]" pageId="11" pageNumber="114">
b) male: genitalia as 
<figureCitation box="[400,474,1100,1122]" captionStart="FIGURE 3" captionStartId="7.[151,250,1943,1967]" captionTargetBox="[214,1368,208,1916]" captionTargetId="figure-18@7.[203,1383,181,1919]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="FIGURE 3. A–B. Genitalia, ventral view; A. Ceropales pallida sp. nov.; B. C. maculata. C–D. Subgenital plate (sternite 8) of male, dorsal view; C. Ceropales pallida sp. nov.; D. C. maculata. E–F. Subgenital plate (sternite 8) of male, lateral view; E. Ceropales pallida sp. nov.; F. C. maculata." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6770940" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6770940/files/figure.png" pageId="11" pageNumber="114">Fig. 3B</figureCitation>
; clypeus with dark median longitudinal stripe (
<figureCitation box="[926,1002,1100,1122]" captionStart="FIGURE 2" captionStartId="6.[151,250,1147,1171]" captionTargetBox="[152,1436,181,1123]" captionTargetId="figure-25@6.[151,1436,181,1123]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="FIGURE 2. A–B. Head of male in frontal view; A. Ceropales pallida sp. nov.; B. C. maculata. C–D. Head of female in dorsal view; C. Ceropales pallida sp. nov.; D. C. maculata." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6770938" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6770938/files/figure.png" pageId="11" pageNumber="114">Fig. 2B</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="11.[151,1436,1012,1180]" pageId="11" pageNumber="114">
- female: antennal segment 1 (scapus) less slender, only slightly longer than broad; tibia 3 with apical third darkened (
<figureCitation box="[1343,1416,1129,1151]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="5.[151,250,1943,1967]" captionTargetBox="[374,1216,183,1919]" captionTargetId="figure-18@5.[371,1216,181,1919]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURE 1. A–C. Habitus of Ceropales. A. Holotype male, Ceropales pallida sp. nov.; B. Female, C. pallida sp. nov; C. Female, C. maculata." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6770936" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6770936/files/figure.png" pageId="11" pageNumber="114">Fig. 1C</figureCitation>
).......................................................................................... 
